How does Harley-Davidson use my personal information?
We may use your personal information in the following ways:
To personalize and enhance your experiences when you interact with Harley-Davidson
To enable Harley-Davidson to provide you with the highest quality experiences, products, services and motorcycles
To process and fulfill your orders, which includes sending you transactional emails to confirm your order status and shipment
To communicate with you and send you information by email, postal mail, telephone (including autodialed or pre-recorded call), text message, or other means about our products, services, contests, and promotions, unless you have directed us not to contact you with promotional communications
To administer contests and promotions, and to respond to your requests
To help us learn more about your motorcycle and retail preferences
To help us manage and improve our websites, events, experiences, products and services
To update you on membership programs, benefits and service
To validate your identity
To alert you about product safety announcement or recall
To perform market and demographic research
To establish or exercise our legal rights or defend against any legal claims, or when necessary, to investigate, prevent, or respond to suspected illegal activities or fraud, or to protect the safety, rights, or property of you, us, or a third party
How long does Harley-Davidson retain my personal information?
The amount of time Harley-Davidson will retain personal information varies, depending on the services Harley-Davidson has provided and the nature of the personal information that Harley-Davidson holds.  Harley-Davidson only retains personal information for such period of time as is necessary for the legitimate purposes for which the personal data are processed.
With respect to the H-D™ Connect Services, Harley-Davidson, Inc. may retain your H-D™ Connect Data for up to 10 years, or, in the case of Vehicle Data, Vehicle Health Data, and Location Data, for up to 15 years from the date the personal data has been collected.
Where you purchase products from us online, we may also retain information about your order history (such as Transaction Data relating to previous orders) for up to 10 years.
Legal requirements, however, may require us to retain some or all of the personal information we hold for a period of time that is longer than that for which we might otherwise hold.
When personal information is no longer required by Harley-Davidson or by law, Harley-Davidson will either convert it into an aggregated non-identifying form or Harley-Davidson will appropriately destroy or erase the personal information.
Does Harley-Davidson share my information?
We may disclose your personal information for certain business purposes as described below:
Our Corporate Family:
We may share your personal information within Harley-Davidson throughout the world  (including with, but not exclusive of, Harley-Davidson Inc., HD U.S.A. LLC, Harley-Davidson Motor Company Group LLC, Harley-Davidson Motor Company Inc., Harley-Davidson Motor Company Operations Inc., and Harley-Davidson Dealer Systems Inc., all of which are based in the USA) to assist us in providing any HD Services to you, offering any personalized experiences, offering products or other services that may be of interest to you, and to process online orders and other requests.
Dealers and HDFS:
We may also share information with our independent dealers and Harley-Davidson Financial Services (HDFS). Please note that if you are a subscriber of the H-D
™
Connect and Vehicle Integration Services and you have a vehicle loan in place with HDFS, in accordance with your agreement with HDFS, we may share the location data of your vehicle with HDFS if you default on your vehicle loan.
Third-Party Partners:
We may also share personal information with our third-party partners to the extent necessary for those providers to provide services to us, including, but not limited to, technology partners, payment partners, marketing agencies, professional advisers and other suppliers. Please note that for the H-D
™
Connect and Vehicle Integration Services we may share H-D™ Connect and Vehicle Integration Data with certain third-party partners that we use to provide the H-D™ Connect and Vehicle Integration Services to the extent necessary to provide the H-D
™
Connect and Vehicle Integration Services, including our network services provider, technology services and storage provider, identity management provider, billing services provider, subscription services provider and third-party providers that support our mobile app. In addition, we may give anonymized data (data that cannot be traced back to you) to third party partners for statistical purposes and for analyzing and improving our services. We take steps to ensure that these companies are contractually obligated to keep the personal information that we provide to them confidential and to use such information only as we permit. We may also share personal information with non-affiliated companies that market Harley-Davidson branded products and services, or in connection with your financial obligations concerning a Harley-Davidson product or service. These companies have their own privacy practices and notices.
Certain Business Transfers:
Your personal information may be disclosed as part of a corporate business transaction, such as a merger, acquisition, or joint venture, or for the financing or sale of Harley-Davidson assets and could be transferred to another party as one of the business assets in such a transaction. It may also be disclosed in the event of insolvency, bankruptcy, or receivership.
Government and Law Enforcement
: We may share your information as required or permitted by law, including sharing with governmental agencies, law enforcement, or authorized third parties, in response to a verified request relating to a criminal investigation or alleged illegal activity or any other activity that may expose us, you, or any other party to legal liability.
SWEEPSTAKES AND CONTESTS
We may use your personal information to send you marketing materials, to conduct surveys, contests, sweepstakes, and to award prizes. We may request additional information to participate in contests and surveys (such as your photos, personal opinions, preferences, and interests). Participation in these surveys or contests is completely voluntary and you may choose whether or not to participate and therefore disclose your information. Contact information will be used to notify the winners and award prizes.
H-D
™
connect and vehicle integration services
The H-D™ Connect and Vehicle Integration Services may not be available in your country of residence, in which case this section will not apply to you.
If you subscribe to the H-D™ Connect Services, we will collect and process certain personal data about you and your vehicle for the purposes of providing the H-D™ Connect Services, as follows (together, the "
H-D™ Connect Data
"). Providing your H-D™ Connect Data to us is voluntary, however, if we do not collect these H-D™ Connect Data, we may not be able to provide you with the H-D™ Connect Services or some of its features that you have requested.
Category of H-D™ Connect Data
Description
Subscriber Information
Information about you, including your name, occupation, gender, age, date of birth, contact information (email, postal address, phone number and mobile phone number), account information (Customer Profile ID, password, alternate contact information (for 2-factor authentication)), driving license details, Harley Owner Group (HOG) membership ID (if any), Museum membership ID (if any), and marketing preferences.
Subscription Data
Information regarding your subscription package, including start and end dates, subscription and features activated/deactivated status, auto renewal status, and subscription history.
Payment Data
Credit card/payment details, issuing bank, expiry date and security code and billing address.
Vehicle Data
Data concerning your vehicle including the Vehicle Identification Number, model, model year, TCU number, selling dealer, and Home/Garage location address.
Vehicle Health Data
Diagnostic data relating to your vehicle. The data points will differ depending on whether the bike is an Electric Vehicle (EV), or Internal Combustion Engine (ICE) vehicle, but could include data such as odometer, fuel range, battery status, tire pressure, ride mode, charging status, and maintenance schedule.
You can manage and set notification alerts in respect of these data points via the mobile app
Location Data
To support the H-D™ Connect Services, we will periodically obtain location data from your vehicle. You should not subscribe to H-D™ Connect if you do not agree to have this location data collected. If you place your vehicle into Stolen Vehicle mode, our systems will collect the location of your vehicle more frequently. You should not place your vehicle into Stolen Vehicle mode if you do not agree to have this location data collected.
Firmware over the Air (FOTA) Updates
Information about software updates that are sent to your vehicle, including whether the update is successful and feedback from you about the update.
Mobile App Data
Your device type, operating system, IP address, the unique identification number, the type of browser, the Internet service provider, information about your use of the app, and location of your device (assuming you have agreed in your device settings to the location of your device).
We may collect and process (and permit our third-party service providers to collect and process) the H-D™ Connect Data for the following purposes in accordance with this Notice and as otherwise permitted or required by law.
